						               													<description>COOPERATION: The Wealth of Nations Game is a boardgame simulating economic systems. It includes four different variants of different skill levels based on different economic systems. BARTER is the beginners' game, MAJORITY RULE is the socialist game, MAKING MONEY is the capitalist game, and AUTONOMY is the expert tournament game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game plays up to six players. Each player manages cities. The object of a game is to obtain basic resources for each city while employing the fewest people . Players receive points for each different resource they obtain and bonus points for citizens at leisure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;AUTONOMY simulates a futuristic possible economic system that would produce wealth for everyone with a minimum of work.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is based on Information Chain Theory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition to existing as a boardgame, this game is downloadable as an electronic game from the publishers' website.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
